# Avoid displaying numbers in scientific notation
options(scipen=999)

data <- read_csv("data/group_04.csv", col_types = cols(
  Urban = col_factor(),
  Historic = col_factor(),
  Material = col_factor(),
))

data <- data |> mutate(
  WPL = Width / Lanes_on,
  Lanes_on = cut(Lanes_on, 
      breaks = c(0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, Inf), 
      labels = c("1", "2","3", "4", "5", "6", "7", "8", ">8"), 
      right = TRUE)
)

test_data <- read_csv("data/test.csv", col_types = cols(
  Urban = col_factor(),
  Historic = col_factor(),
  Material = col_factor(),
))

test_data <- test_data |> mutate(
  WPL = Width / Lanes_on,
  Lanes_on = cut(Lanes_on, 
                 breaks = c(0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, Inf), 
                 labels = c("1", "2","3", "4", "5", "6", "7", "8", ">8"), 
                 right = TRUE)
)

predict_test <- function(model) {
  pred <- predict(model, newdata = test_data)

  # Evaluate (example: RMSE)
  rmse <- sqrt(mean((test_data$Condition - pred)^2))
  rmse
}

# Interaction:
# AverageDaily * WPL: The amount of daily traffic may affect condition more if the bridge is narrow as more cars fit into less space
# Spans * Length: Longer bridge with more spans (i.e. more stable) may be healthier than those with less spans
# AverageDaily * Material: High amount of daily traffic with less strong material may lead to worse bridge condition.
# Trucks_percent * Material: Same as above
model3 <- lm(Condition ~ Urban + Historic +
               Year + log(AverageDaily + 1)* log(WPL + 1) + 
               log(Spans + 1) * log(Length + 1) +
               log(Trucks_percent + 1) * Material +
               log(AverageDaily + 1) * Material + 
               Lanes_on, data = dplyr::select(data, -c(Structure_id, Width)))

model3.standardized <- lm.beta(model3)
